Thus, IL-6 is an important mediator in inhibition of osteoblast differentiation by
TNFα and knockdown of IL-6 partially rescues osteogenesis from negative control of
inflammation. The anti-osteoblastic effects of IL-6 are most likely mediated by its
negative interaction with Wnt signaling pathway.
